      "date": "2013-10-30 04:26:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nShadow, I would say although it's not a one-shot solution but it is a good step for resolving the reported issue. It should be able to greatly increase speed of draining queued message, which is essential goal of the JIRA ticket. Even we really need to have a full implementation of message abort in the future, this patch will not has any conflict, so honestly, I don't see why it has to be denied at here.",
